metadata.name: Jubilee #111
metadata.description:
Jubilee is a flow field festival celebrating creation. Ribbons scattered through a space meet one another, overlap, and are generally at the mercy of the forces acting upon them. But collectively, what complex forms can they create?

Canvas size is 1200 x 1600 pixels, in either portrait or landscape.

To change canvas size:

[1] 1200 x 1600 
[2] 2400 x 3200 
[3] 4800 x 6400

[s] will save a png at the chosen resolution.

metadata.name: For Better Dreams #2
metadata.description:
A radiant talisman. Watchful third eye. Use as directed.

Once minted your patterns maintain their design while stretching to accommodate changes in canvas size.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone. That aside, there are 6 possible color palettes and 7 possible background colors. 

This artwork was created using p5js and utilizes the p5.pattern library created by Taichi Sayama.

linktr.ee/lisaorthstudio
twitter: @lisaorthstudio

metadata.name: Redundancy #77
metadata.description:
This generative token explores redundancy as an architectural concept, method, and process. Redundancy provides flexibility in an open form, enabling a shift from monofunctional to multifunctional as well as from optimized to resilient. A hybrid architecture in which complexity is created through the continuous reconfiguration of simple discrete and compatible blocks.
Each minted redundancy token reveals various deterministic rare features, styles, and scales, creating endlessly redundant open architectures. 

Redundancy Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: White Night Vol.1 #152
metadata.description:
I have a long-term photography project called “White Night”, which explores special images of trees through black and white inversion.

I attempt to generate similar images by code, and this is the start of the journey.

Made with p5js.

Controls:
- Press “f” to toggle the frame, there is my signature on the mat inside the frame.
- Press “s” to save the image displayed at that moment as a PNG file.
- Change the canvas size by adding “size” URL parameter, for example: &size=1000 (you may add this and lower the number if your device can’t render properly)

metadata.name: Make-believe #4
metadata.description:
#genuary32nd – Let's meet on this make-believe date, in this make-believe place.
I’m having déjà vu, or is it a memory?

This artwork is originally created for the genuary2023 prompt "Art Deco", using the same core algorithm as Memory Module. Made with fractal math and p5js.

Keyboard controls:
[s] Save the current view in live mode.
[1] to [8] Change resolution, 1.5K to 12K.
[g] Toggle texture.

URL params:
&aspect=[aspect ratio, eg 2]
&res=[resolution multiplier, 0.5-8]

Created by Elsif, 2023.02

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl

metadata.name: Vormen #31
metadata.description:
“Vormen” can mean two things in Dutch. It is either the plural of the noun shape or, it a verb that means something like to form, to create, to sculpt or to shape. With this artwork, you can freely “vorm” the “vormen”. 

Your "vorm" will always be centered and you can use the custom minting interface to easily change it to your liking. This is MathBirds submission for the fxhackathon.

metadata.name: Paysages Chromatiques A #46
metadata.description:
Taking my inspiration from impressionist and contemporary paintings, I tried to generate 
mixtures of more or less superimposed colors, creating flowing effects or spots as one
would obtain with paint.
This work is the first in a two-part series featuring abstraction and imagination.
I hope it will inspire you to take the time to daydream, or simply to spend a moment 
where the mind can wander freely through the colors.

To save a png file type [s]
TO remove the texture type [t]

To render at higher resolution add &pd=2 at the end of the url in live mode
(others values are valid too but be patient the rendering can be long)
---
100% code made with p5js and glsl
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.
---
